Mosaic release: v7

Mirrored from https://s3.amazonaws.com/grizli-v2/JwstMosaics/v7/index.html , which might be slightly more up to date than this list.

What's new?

18 September 2024

  • ceers-full-grizli-v7.4 Updated mosaic with newer imaging data, including GO-2234 (PI: Bañados)
  • PRIMER UDS north and south with v7.2
  • nexus-nep-grizli-v7.4 from GO-5105 (PI: Shen)
  • Updated spitzer_idf-grizli-v7.4 ( GTO-2738 , PI: Windhorst)
  • Additional lensing cluster fields abell1689-grizli-v7.4 | sunburst-grizli-v7.2, plck-g165p67-v7.4, tn-j1338m1942-v7.4, clg-1212p2733-v7.4, plck-g191p62-v7.4 , gama100033-v7.4

19 Februrary 2024

  • Updated GOODS-N mosaics gdn-grizli-v7.3 in-place to include F090W, F115W, and F356W imaging data from GO-3577 .

08 Februrary 2024

  • Updated GOODS-N mosaics ( gdn-grizli-v7.3 ) with newly-available NIRCam and MIRI imaging from the JADES GTO-1181 program. The mosaic was expanded slightly from the previous version, so new HST mosaics were generated as well.
  • ngdeep-grizli-v7.2 includes the second epoch of NIRCam imaging from Jan 2024 for GO-2079.
  • CEERS regenerated with v7.2 improvements

12 December 2023

  • Updated Abell 2744 mosaics to include new F070W, F090W, medium-band, and NIRISS imaging from Cycle 2 programs GO-2883 (PI: Sun), GO-3516 (PI: Matthee), GO-3538 (PI: Iani), and GO-4111 (PI: Suess).
    • Version 7.1 was the first pass through much of these new data
    • Version 7.2 is the latest pass that includes updated NIRCam and NIRISS snowball masking with snowblind as described and implemented here . That grizli update also includes updated NIRCam SW and LW bad pixel masks.
  • The field gds-sw , version 7.0, includes deep NIRCam imaging from GO-3215 (PI: Eisenstein), and the version 7.1 mosaic on the original gds footprint also includes some of these data at the edges.

26 September 2023

  • Add HST mosaics and shallow JWST NIRCam mosaics ( GO-1840, PI: Alvarez-Marquez) of the lensing cluster Abell S1063 (abells1063)

24 August 2023

  • Add missing HST/ACS exposures to gds and ngdeep and update photometric catalogs

14 August 2023

  • PRIMER August 2023 (primer-uds, primer-cosmos)
    • Mosaics in both fields split in half, with overlaps, to facilitate catalog generation. Both halves created with a common tangent point.
      primer-cosmos-east / west

      primer-uds-north / south
    • All mosaics still have 40mas pixels, both SW and LW
    • HST mosaics created on the updated pixel grids
    • UDS includes the most recent visits from August 2023
    • All JWST PRIMER-UDS have been fully reprocessed with the following modifications
      • Individual Level1 NIRCam exposures reprocessed with improved treatment of the snowballs ( grizli.jwst_level1)
      • All PRIMER visits aligned to a new full astrometric catalog generated from the F444W mosaic, which itself was aligned to the HSC ultra-deep i-band catalog.
    • Added eazy photoz outputs for the new PRIMER mosaics (16 Aug 2023)
  • Added mosaics of the elgordo field ( ACT CLJ0102-49151, GTO-1176)

July 2023

  • Mosaics created with the new jwst weighting strategy to address the issues described here and here
  • Catalogs and photometric redshifts in prep (14 July 2023)
  • Abell 2744
    • Expanded mosaic footprint to include all available JWST data
    • Mosaics include data from GLASS obtained July 2023
  • GOODS-North (gdn)
    • Includes a few pointings from the PANORAMIC (GO-2514) pure parallel program
  • GOODS-South (gds)
    • Includes all public imaging data from the FRESCO (GO-1895), JEMS (GO-1963) and JADES (GTO-1210) programs.
  • PRIMER (primer-uds, primer-cosmos)
    • COSMOS cosaic expanded w.r.t. v6 to encompass the full PRIMER NIRCam + MIRI mosaic, now including both epochs/orientations.
    • The mosaics in both PRIMER fields are huge! NIRCam SW mosaics in both PRIMER fields are created with the same 40 mas pixel grid as LW.
    • Updated HST mosaics included here on the new COSMOS pixel grid. UDS is unchanged from v6.
    • Some improvement in the PRIMER MIRI reductions using time-dependent sky flats.
